## What Changes

Memory configuration becomes agent-owned instead of global. `agents.defaults.memory` defines the baseline; `agents.list[].memory` is the per-agent override.

### Before

```jsonc
{
  "memory": { "backend": "qmd", "qmd": { /* ... */ } },
  "memorySearch": { "provider": "openai", /* ... */ },
  "agents": {
    "defaults": { "memorySearch": { /* ... */ } },
    "list": [
      { "id": "research", "memorySearch": { /* ... */ }, "dreaming": { "enabled": true } }
    ]
  }
}
```

### After

```jsonc
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "memory": {
        "backend": "builtin",
        "search": { "provider": "openai", /* ... */ },
        "extensions": {
          "memory-core": { "dreaming": { "enabled": false } }
        }
      }
    },
    "list": [
      {
        "id": "research",
        "memory": {
          "backend": "qmd",
          "qmd": { /* ... */ },
          "extensions": {
            "memory-core": { "dreaming": { "enabled": true } }
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

`memory.search.store.path` is removed. Builtin indexes live in the selected agent's database rather than a configurable SQLite sidecar.

### Runtime Behavior

- The resolved agent selects the memory backend, search/index configuration, QMD collections and startup, dreaming, Memory Wiki state, promotion work, context/citations, and the Dreams UI.
- Defaults apply to every agent; an entry in `agents.list[].memory` overrides that agent only.
- Dreaming is scheduled only for resolved agents with dreaming enabled. An all-agent opt-out stays opted out; the default-agent fallback is used only when no valid configured agent exists.
- Gateway and UI requests carry the target agent identity. Unknown gateway agents are rejected rather than falling back to another agent's memory.
- Dream artifacts are excluded from builtin and QMD indexing, including configured cross-workspace extra paths. Shared-workspace handling is keyed by the physical workspace to avoid cross-agent leakage.

### Doctor And Migration

Use `openclaw doctor --lint` to detect legacy configuration, then `openclaw doctor --fix` to migrate it.

- Top-level `memory` moves to `agents.defaults.memory`; top-level and default `memorySearch` move to `agents.defaults.memory.search`.
- Per-agent `memorySearch` and `dreaming` move under `agents.list[].memory`, with dreaming becoming `memory.extensions.memory-core.dreaming`.
- When both shapes are present, doctor fills missing fields from legacy config and keeps explicit agent-scoped values.
- Legacy `provider: "auto"` becomes `"openai"`; legacy `memorySearch.store.path` is removed because indexes now use the agent database.
- Memory Core migrates unscoped dreaming state and legacy dream diaries into agent-scoped state. Memory Wiki migrates its source-sync and import-run state into the agent-scoped store.
- State migration preserves existing agent entries, archives migrated file sources as `*.migrated`, and warns instead of guessing when a shared workspace cannot be attributed to its resolved default agent.

### Validation

- Focused regression suites cover Memory Core, memory-host SDK, gateway startup/agent validation, and Dreams UI agent selection.
- `pnpm check:changed` passed in Blacksmith Testbox before the final two-file privacy follow-up; the final retry passed structural checks and typecheck but ended with Testbox exit 255 before reporting a failed lane.
